summary: :) I have to say this is one of my fave pics I've made. Janet's team; Litten (her fave Starter), Talonflame (she favors Fire...
caption:
:) I have to say this is one of my fave pics I’ve made.

Janet’s team;

Litten (her fave Starter), Talonflame (she favors Fire type Pokemon), Lycanroc (to resemble her pet Dalmatian, Garlic)

Lisa’s team;

Bunnelby (to resemble her pet rabbit, Bounce), Popplio (she favors Water Starter Pokemon; I wanted to actually put Brionne but the pen had a head start), Combee (1. It’s the nickname her dad calls her, and 2. She’s that busy at times)

Casey’s team;

Treecko (it reminded me a little of Casey in looks so why not?), female Meowstic (to resemble his pet Calico cat, Mrs. Princess), Drampa (a fatherly figure to Casey, not that Casey’s real father doesn’t love him, mind you)

Martha’s team;

Serperior (surprisingly fits her well; But she don’t got a pet snake but she does have a St Bernard, Bernard and Cockatoo, Eugene), Herdier (to resemble her Scottish background from her dad’s side of the family, and the fact her cousin has a Scottish Terrier, Tavish), shiny Roserade (the colors perfectly resemble the Asexual flag, so it’s a good pick for Martha)

https://carlycmarathecat.tumblr.com/post/181267293410/d-presenting-the-sequel-marthas-team#notes

body:
The astrological charts are basically the same in every region, based on the legendary Pokemon throughout the world

January 20 - February 17:  Lugia

February 18- March 20: Manaphy

March 19 - April 20:  Xerneas

April 21 - May 21:  Terrakion

May 22 - June 21:  Latios and Latias

June 22 - July 22: Kyogre

July 23 - August 23: Entei

August 24 - September 23: Celebi

September 24 - October 23: Ho-Oh

October 24 - November 22: Giratina

November 23- December 22: Cresselia 

December 23- January 20: Virizion


The only region this differs in Unova, where the chart looks like this:

January 20 - February 17:  Milotic

February 18- March 20:  Phione

March 19 - April 20:  Gogoat

April 21 - May 21: Tauros

May 22 - June 21:  Plusle and Minun

June 22 - July 22: Kingler

August 24 - September 23: Victini

September 24 - October 23: Jirachi

October 24 - November 22: Darkrai

November 23- December 22: Decidueye

December 23- January 20: Shaymin

summary: Plauroma (From "plague" and "aroma")  "Where female Spritzee evolve into Aromatisse, male Spritzee evolve into Plauroma - a...
caption:
Plauroma (From “plague” and “aroma”) 

“Where female Spritzee evolve into Aromatisse, male Spritzee evolve into Plauroma - a Pokemon well-known for its ability to cure disease. However, its cloak-like feathers carry many of these diseases where it goes, so it is recommended to be careful around it. It uses its walking cane to attack, if it needs to - but it rarely does, as disease usually gets to whoever it targets.”

“This Pokemon’s face is rumored to not be its actual face at all by some, but rather a mask. From its nostrils, it is capable of expelling sweet-smelling fumes that can either heal or kill whoever breathes them in - and Plauroma chooses what effect its breath has. It carries its walking cane with it wherever it goes, but never seems to need to use it.”

So while my brain was on the subject of making plague-doctor-aesthetic-influenced Pokemon (partially because of these funky little things from yesterday), someone in the art Discord I frequent suggested that male Spritzee could have been the ones to evolve into the plague-doctor types - I kinda liked the idea, so I did my own take on it, hence these classy gentlemen :D

(I know it reinforces gender roles somewhat, but heck - who says Plauroma can’t be dancers, and Aromatisse can’t be doctors?)
